To use this standalone C++/ROOT analysis framework created for SLAC 2016, simply git clone the whole repository:

git clone https://github.com/kimsiang/SLAC2016

Then go to the SLAC2016Ana/ folder and execute the following command:

make clean; make

Insert the root file (currently gm2uw_run01865_analysis.root) that you want to analyze into the input.script file and analyze the file by running

./ana input.script

Variables that can be accessed from the root file are defined in EventCollection.h. You can add your analysis codes to the file SLAC2016Ana.C and SLAC2016Ana.h.
